We can explain GitOps in simple, powerful terms.
We treat Git as the single source of truth for our entire infrastructure.

We make every change through a Pull Request, and once it is approved, the system updates itself automatically.

We get clean history, full transparency, easy rollback, and zero manual guesswork.
GitOps evolved from traditional DevOps and IaC. 
